# Desktop horizontal UI preference

## When this applies

Estimate workspace surfaces, AI review/confirmation dialogs, and other ShopRally CRM modals/panels shown primarily on desktop (≥1024px).

## Layout rule

- **Prefer horizontal composition** when horizontal space exists — use 2- or 3-column grids, side-by-side context + action panels, or full-width strips with multi-column content below.
- **Avoid tall single-column modals** on desktop (narrow `max-w-lg` phone-style stacks) when the content has distinct sections (e.g. source text + selectable suggestions).
- **Stack vertically only at narrow breakpoints** (`md` / `lg` and below) — mobile-first responsive, but desktop is the primary target for estimate-building UX.

## Patterns

| Surface | Desktop layout |
|---------|----------------|
| AI review dialogs | Left context rail (source/description) + right suggestion columns (Concerns \| Jobs & Parts) |
| Estimate panels | Side-by-side toolbars, grids, and review cards — not one long scroll column |
| Wide dialogs | `max-w-4xl`–`max-w-5xl`, not `max-w-lg` |

## Brand + quality

Follow `.cursor/rules/design-quality-bar.mdc` — structural layout changes, ShopRally navy / light-blue / red. Do not remove confirmation/review steps for AI or pricing writes.
